 "narrative": "V1 and V2 were traveling north bound on a four lane, physically divided, bidirectional roadway, with two lanes north bound and two lanes south bound. Both vehicles were negotiating a curve to the right, with a slight incline to the roadway. V1 was traveling in lane one, while V2 was traveling in lane two. V1 began to move into lane two as V2 was attempting to pass it. V2 departed its lane to the right, where  V2's frontal plane impacted V1's rear plane. V2 came to final rest off of the right side of the roadway. There was a small fire in the engine compartment of V2. V1 continued north bound and was not located.",
